This paper is about an online AI/ATP service for formal mathematics encoded in the HOL Light system. It discusses the use of automated reasoning systems and premise selection methods, which are topics related to logic and artificial intelligence (cs.LO and cs.AI). The paper also mentions an Emacs interface, which suggests a focus on programming languages and software engineering (cs.PL and cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the system's performance, which could be related to distributed systems (cs.DS).
